Not a gaming mouse. Not a 3D mouse clone.

A platform.

Base

Normal ergonomic mouse.

USB-C.

F-Mouse internals.

Left magnetic rail

Attach different modules:

🎛 Rotary encoder

🎮 Mini joystick

🖲 Trackball

⌨ 3-key macro pad

🎚 Slider


Swap in 2 seconds.

Software

Profiles:

CAD

KiCad

Blender

Shotcut

VS Code


The OLED says:

BLENDER
Encoder → Zoom
Key1 → G
Key2 → R
Key3 → S

Switch to CAD:

ONSHAPE
Encoder → Rotate
Key1 → Pan
Key2 → Fit
Key3 → Measure
Now ask: Would people buy it?

I think yes.

Because people don't buy a new mouse every time they change workflows.

Why I like it for Fallout:

Great industrial design challenge.

PCB challenge.

Firmware challenge.

Mechanical design.

Product thinking.

Beautiful renders.

Expandable ecosystem.

And the documentation almost writes itself.

My only simplification:

Don't actually design every module.

Design:

Base mouse.

Magnetic interface.

One rotary encoder module.

One macro pad module.


Show that more modules can exist later.

That is enough to communicate the platform.

# Tagline: A modular input platform.

